    "recap_headline": "Boston College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "RALEIGH, N.C. -\nBoston College Baseball (11-7, 3-2 ACC) defeated NC State (15-4, 1-1 ACC) on Saturday afternoon, 12-5.\nTyler Mudd\nstarted for the Eagles and went three innings while giving up three earned runs and striking out one. He induced his other eight outs all through fly outs.\nKyle Kipp\ncame in relief and threw three innings while giving up two earned runs.\nJohn Kwiatkowski\nand\nGavin Soares\nclosed the game out, combining to allow two hits and two strikeouts without giving up a run.\nNick Wang\ngot Boston College on the board as he hit his ninth home run of the season to put the Eagles up 1-0 in the top of the first inning.\nThe Wolfpack took their first lead of the game in the bottom of the second with three runs. The first two runs came on sacrifice flies after Mudd loaded up the bases for NC State. The final run came on a single to right field that brought in a runner from second, putting the Wolfpack ahead 3-1.\nIn the fourth, Boston College put up three runs to take a 4-3 lead into the fifth inning. Jace Roosien, for the second straight game, came on as a pinch hitter and hit a single to right field that scored two runs, giving Roosien three home runs for the series.\nColin Larson\nthen knocked another single to right field to score Roosien and give the Eagles the lead.\nThe game remained the same through the fifth and sixth innings until NC State retook the lead 5-4. The Wolfpack tied the game on a solo shot to right field. They then went ahead on a single to left field.\nThe eighth inning proved to be decisive for Boston College as they put up eight runs to take over the game. The Eagles tied the game when\nEsteban Garcia's\ninfield single was thrown away by NC State, allowing\nTy Mainolfi\nto score from third. During the very next at-bat, Wang scored on a passed ball to make it 6-5.\nColin Larson\nthen launched a three-run triple to center field to make it 9-5. After the Larson triple, the Eagles put runners on second and third for Mainolfi after they batted around. Mainolfi then launched his first home run at Boston College to deep center field, which scored Larson and\nJulio Solier\nto make it 12-5.\nSoares then came in for the bottom of the eighth to close out the game.\nUp Next:\nThe Eagles will return to action tomorrow at 12:00 p.m. for the finale of the three-game series against the Wolfpack."
  },
